HEADWORD: Hydration
<hw>Hy*dra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>The act of becoming, or state of being, a hydrate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Water of hydration</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>,
<cd>water chemically combined with some substance to form a hydrate; --
distinguished from <contr>water of
crystallization</contr>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydraulic</ent>⟦br⟧
